\begin_layout Standard
In general terms, the cybernetic agents seeks to reach equilibrium by moving
 across the environmental space or by tracking some specific point therein
 in case of a dynamically evolving space.
 It follows that a minimal cybernetic model would always have to provide,
 in addition to the external and internal spaces (the environment and the
 agent, resp), a set of actions that move the latter across the former.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Sound domain translation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The translation of the concept to the sound domain starts with the basic
 concepts sketched above: the environmental space, the agent, and the actions.
\end_layout

