\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A sound space can be defined by keeping the values of a subset of the five
 parameters fix and lets the others vary.
 A mono-dimensional frequency space, for instance, could be defined as the
 the space of sounds of different pitch but fixed duration, timbre, location,
 and intensity (and similarly for the mono-dimensional intensity space,
 duration space, etc.).
 The minimal working setup of the Braitenberg-1 type detailed below will
 use a one-dimensional sound space of this sort.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection

\emph on
